It's depressing to know that while all the "sheeple" are listening to this horsesh*t, bands/musicians with actual talent are forced to perform on train stations and in the back corners of pubs...

I love all the people jumping on the bandwagon yelling "sheeple" at people downloading this, when they're clearly just trying to fit in with the crowd. 

Has it ever occurred to you that some of us "sheeple" might have a degree in classical brass performance, or sound engineering? 

Don't assume so much, some people are just more capable of being open to new ideas than others.

Actually music is meant for experimenting, expressing your points of view, letting the world know about your emotions, or all of them together. LMFAO does none of that. Public Enemy, and Gang Starr express their points of view. Tiesto, Datsik, 12th Planet, and Skrillex experiment with new sounds and effects. Korn shows extreme emotion in their music and let the whole world listen to Jonathan Davis's emotions. Nine Inch Nails and TV on the Radio express all three. LMFAO does not. Don't even tell me they experiment because their sound is sketchy. I'd rather listen to Christian music than listen to LMFAO. There is always good music in every Genre but LMFAO is a joke. And it's pretty sad that despite Wuzzard's degree in music, he/she does not know how to define good music. Artists like LMFAO, Drake, Lil' Wayne, etc. are slaughtering music and changing into something unbearable. The world needs to stop "following the leader" and needs to start being original because our originality is what defines us.

@Wuzzard
